1
02:44:58,009 --> 02:44:59,090
[WHISPERING] Hello?

2
02:45:04,769 --> 02:45:05,850
[KNOCKS ECHOING]

3
02:45:14,369 --> 02:45:15,780
[CLEARS THROAT]

4
02:45:18,129 --> 02:45:19,540
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
He's not at home.

5
02:45:20,489 --> 02:45:22,173
Not at home. Ahem.

6
02:45:23,009 --> 02:45:24,090
Good.

7
02:45:25,889 --> 02:45:27,618
Good, good, good.

8
02:46:22,605 --> 02:46:23,620
What's that?

9
02:46:26,489 --> 02:46:28,457
Shush. Shush.

10
02:46:29,769 --> 02:46:31,055
Arkenstone.

11
02:46:32,089 --> 02:46:33,500
Arkenstone.

12
02:46:34,329 --> 02:46:36,377
A large, white jewel.

13
02:46:38,569 --> 02:46:39,934
Very helpful.

14
02:47:18,089 --> 02:47:19,579
[SMAUG EXHALES]

15
02:48:55,449 --> 02:48:57,213
[SNIFFING]

16
02:49:05,911 --> 02:49:07,322
Well...

17
02:49:08,609 --> 02:49:09,895
...thief.

18
02:49:11,889 --> 02:49:15,530
I smell you.

19
02:49:15,889 --> 02:49:19,098
I hear your breath.

20
02:49:20,714 --> 02:49:24,664
I feel your air.

21
02:49:27,504 --> 02:49:30,030
Where are you?

22
02:49:31,503 --> 02:49:32,584
Where are you?

23
02:49:52,695 --> 02:49:56,217
Come now, don't be shy.

24
02:49:56,825 --> 02:49:59,032
Step into the light.

25
02:50:03,600 --> 02:50:04,203
Hmm.

26
02:50:06,038 --> 02:50:09,247
There is something about you.

27
02:50:12,584 --> 02:50:14,466
Something you carry.

28
02:50:15,249 --> 02:50:18,139
Something made of gold.

29
02:50:18,889 --> 02:50:21,813
But far more...

30
02:50:22,049 --> 02:50:23,858
...precious.

31
02:50:24,089 --> 02:50:26,410
VOICE OF THE RING:
<i>Precious! Precious!</i>

32
02:50:29,209 --> 02:50:30,370
There you are...

33
02:50:30,649 --> 02:50:34,252
...Thief in the Shadows.

34
02:50:36,089 --> 02:50:38,695
I did not come to steal from you...

35
02:50:39,159 --> 02:50:42,420
...O Smaug the Unassessably Wealthy.

36
02:50:42,952 --> 02:50:45,350
I merely wanted to gaze upon your magnificence.

37
02:50:45,909 --> 02:50:49,648
To see if you really were
as great as the old tales say.

38
02:50:50,209 --> 02:50:51,938
[WHIMPERS] I did not believe them.

39
02:51:00,769 --> 02:51:04,694
And do you now?!

40
02:51:06,049 --> 02:51:07,289
Truly...

41
02:51:08,609 --> 02:51:10,816
...the tales and songs...

42
02:51:12,371 --> 02:51:17,796
...fall utterly short of your enormity
O Smaug the Stupendous.

43
02:51:18,089 --> 02:51:20,979
Do you think flattery will keep you alive?

44
02:51:21,489 --> 02:51:22,456
No, no.

45
02:51:22,689 --> 02:51:24,179
No, indeed.

46
02:51:26,449 --> 02:51:29,692
You seem familiar with my name...

47
02:51:29,929 --> 02:51:32,819
...but I don't remember smelling
your kind before.

48
02:51:34,358 --> 02:51:38,295
Who are you, and where do you come from...

49
02:51:38,757 --> 02:51:40,850
...may I ask?

50
02:51:50,409 --> 02:51:52,093
I come from under the hill.

51
02:51:52,722 --> 02:51:54,133
Underhill?

52
02:51:57,569 --> 02:52:00,691
BILBO: And under hills and
over hills my path has led.

53
02:52:01,569 --> 02:52:02,411
And... And...

54
02:52:03,169 --> 02:52:05,536
...through the air.
I am he who walks unseen.

55
02:52:05,769 --> 02:52:07,498
Impressive.

56
02:52:08,080 --> 02:52:10,782
What else do you claim to be?

57
02:52:11,150 --> 02:52:12,413
I--I am...

58
02:52:14,769 --> 02:52:16,259
Luck-wearer.

59
02:52:17,883 --> 02:52:19,044
Riddle-maker.

60
02:52:19,441 --> 02:52:21,091
Lovely titles.

61
02:52:21,785 --> 02:52:22,946
<i>Go on.</i>

62
02:52:23,280 --> 02:52:24,361
Barrel-rider.

63
02:52:24,561 --> 02:52:27,963
Barrels? Now that is interesting.

64
02:52:29,584 --> 02:52:33,059
And what about your little Dwarf friends?

65
02:52:34,442 --> 02:52:36,759
Where are they hiding?

66
02:52:38,289 --> 02:52:39,859
Dwarves?

67
02:52:40,689 --> 02:52:41,770
No.

68
02:52:42,651 --> 02:52:45,492
No, no. No Dwarves here.
You've got that all wrong.

69
02:52:45,871 --> 02:52:49,335
Oh, I don't think so, Barrel-rider!

70
02:52:50,107 --> 02:52:53,104
They sent you in here to do their dirty work...

71
02:52:53,385 --> 02:52:56,140
...while they skulk about outside.

72
02:52:56,809 --> 02:52:57,970
Truly...

73
02:52:58,769 --> 02:53:03,692
...you are mistaken, O Smaug,
Chiefest and Greatest of Calamities.

74
02:53:03,934 --> 02:53:06,851
You have nice manners...

75
02:53:07,424 --> 02:53:08,772
...for a thief...

76
02:53:09,130 --> 02:53:10,638
...and a liar!

77
02:53:11,569 --> 02:53:14,971
I know the smell and taste of Dwarf.

78
02:53:15,838 --> 02:53:17,666
<i>No one better!</i>

79
02:53:18,329 --> 02:53:19,740
It is the gold!

80
02:53:20,205 --> 02:53:24,522
They are drawn to treasure
like flies to dead flesh.

81
02:53:27,744 --> 02:53:30,539
Did you think I did not
know this day would come?!

82
02:53:32,841 --> 02:53:37,810
That a pack of canting Dwarves
would come crawling back...

83
02:53:38,369 --> 02:53:39,701
...to the mountain?!

